    "id": "sts-40",
    "title": "STS-40",
    "program": "Space Shuttle",
    "era": "Shuttle Era",
    "year": 1991,
    "launchDate": "1991",
    "description": "1991 American crewed spaceflight",
    "extract": "STS-40, the eleventh launch of Space Shuttle Columbia, was a nine-day mission in June 1991. It carried the Spacelab module for Spacelab Life Sciences 1 (SLS-1), the fifth Spacelab mission and the first dedicated solely to biology. STS-40 was the first spaceflight that included three women crew members.",
