    "title": "SpaceX Crew-3",
    "program": "Commercial Crew",
    "era": "Commercial Crew",
    "year": 2021,
    "launchDate": "2021",
    "description": "2021 American crewed spaceflight to the ISS and maiden flight of Crew Dragon Endurance",
    "extract": "SpaceX Crew-3 was the Crew Dragon's third NASA Commercial Crew operational flight, and its fifth overall crewed orbital flight. The mission successfully launched on November 11, 2021, at 02:03:31 UTC to the International Space Station. It was the maiden flight of Crew Dragon Endurance. This launch brought the total number of humans who have been to space to more than 600 with Maurer (600) and Barron (601).",
